    {"id":"post_1","type":"sharp_opinion","source_theme":"churn_begins_in_sales","text":"Owner churn gets blamed on operations when the real failure was sold into the relationship before the contract was signed.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"sharpest_observation","best_timing":"early_week","publish_after_linkedin":false,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"revenue_operations","source_file":"linkedin/post_1.txt","theme":"churn_begins_in_sales","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_2","type":"recognition","source_theme":"separate_businesses_problem","text":"Many VRMs under 100 doors aren't running one company. They're running marketing, sales, and ops as three separate businesses that happen to share a logo.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"recognition_line","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"revenue_operations","source_file":"linkedin/post_2.txt","theme":"separate_businesses_problem","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_2.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_3","type":"diagnostic","source_theme":"handoff_audit","text":"Useful audit: ask your BD rep and your PM to separately write the top three expectations of the same new owner. If the lists don't match, the churn clock is already running.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"tactical_question","best_timing":"after_post_1","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"revenue_operations","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"handoff_audit","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_4","type":"story_detail","source_theme":"first_90_days","text":"The first 90 days are still part of the sale. The owner is meeting the company they actually bought, which is often a very different company than the one they were pitched.","engagement_prompt":false,"post_role":"story_detail","best_timing":"mid_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"revenue_operations","source_file":"linkedin/post_1.txt","theme":"first_90_days","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
    {"id":"post_5","type":"engagement","source_theme":"promise_reality_gap","text":"Where do you see the biggest promise-reality gap causing downstream churn: revenue projections, communication cadence, or vague 'care' promises that nobody operationalized?","engagement_prompt":true,"post_role":"conversation_opener","best_timing":"late_week","publish_after_linkedin":true,"source_trace":{"book_slug":"revenue_operations","source_file":"newsletter/newsletter.txt","theme":"promise_reality_gap","related_linkedin_post":"linkedin/post_1.txt"}},
